abstract: Examination of server that housed Hillary Rodham Clinton's personal email account during her tenure as secretary of state shows that there are no copies of any emails she sent during her time in office.
lead_paragraph: The House Select Committee on Benghazi had subpoenaed the server to determine which Hillary Rodham Clinton emails were personal and which were government records.

headline.main: No Copies of Clinton Emails on Server, Lawyer Says
headline.print_headline: No Emails From Clinton’s Time at State Dept. Are on Her Server, Lawyer Says
